   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Document: a document (not a letter) neither in the author's handwriting nor signed by the author ]">D</abbr>, in Joseph Reeds writing, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Draft: a draft of a letter or document in the handwriting of someone other than the author ]">Df</abbr>, in Joseph Reeds writing, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. National Archives and Records Administration, Papers of the Continental Congress, Washington, D.C. ]">DNA:PCC</span>, item 33;

copy in Joseph Reeds writing, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. National Archives and Records Administration, Papers of the Continental Congress, Washington, D.C. ]">DNA:PCC</span>, item 33;

copy in Stephen Moylans writing, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Huntington Library, Art Collections and Botanical Gardens, San Marino, Calif. ]">CSmH</span>;

copy in Edmund Randolphs writing, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Massachusetts Historical Society, Boston ]">MHi</span>: Washington Papers;

copy, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Connecticut State Library, Hartford ]">Ct</span>: Trumbull Papers.

The copies in the Huntington Library, the Massachusetts Historical Society, and the Connecticut State Library do not include the minutes for 2324 October. They were apparently made for various New England governments. Moylans copy may have been enclosed in his letter to Matthew Thornton of 4 Nov. 1775 or his letter to a committee of the Massachusetts council that same date (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>). Randolphs copy was probably enclosed in GW to Nicholas Cooke, 2 Nov. 1775, and the one in the Connecticut State Library is a copy of the copy enclosed in GW to Jonathan Trumbull, Sr., 2 Nov. 1775. Congress apparently used the copy in PCC in its deliberations between 4 Nov. and 22 December. Charles Thomson noted Congresss actions beside many of the items on this copy and changed the wording of some of the committees answers as directed by the delegates.</p>

